    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sculptors in colonial Latin America who created religious figures, usually representations of Christ, the Virgin, saints and angels for altars, processions, nativity, and passion scenes. Imagineros worked with a variety of materials including stone, bone, ceramic and shell, but primarily with polychromed wood.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
